David Ngcobo, alias Nasty C, has released a new track, 'Palm Trees', off his highly anticipated album 'Zulu Man With Some Power'. The album is set to be released via Def Jam Recordings on August 28. Quoted by Billboard as “South Africa’s best bet for a mainstream crossover,” Nasty C has been delivering hit after hit, with 'Palm Trees' being the next single to take Nasty C global. With over 120 million streams worldwide and 3 million followers on social media, Nasty C is one of South Africa’s hottest exports. Nicknamed ‘The Coolest Kid In Africa’, he has already secured support and praise from some of UK’s biggest tastemakers like Charlie Sloth, DJ Semtex and Tim Westwood. He is now on the verge of a global breakthrough.